text: Khorrami (, also Romanized as Khorramī; also known as Khurami) is a village in Arabkhaneh Rural District, Shusef District, Nehbandan County, South Khorasan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 53, in 18 families. == References == Category:Populated places in Nehbandan County
title: Khorrami
